HEADWORD: Tectology
<hw>Tec*tol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
carpenter + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A division
of morphology created by Haeckel; the science of organic individuality
constituting the purely structural portion of morphology, in which the
organism is regarded as composed of organic individuals of different
orders, each organ being considered an individual. See
<er>Promorphology</er>, and <er>Morphon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tectonic</ent>⟦br⟧
